# auto-reply scheduled drafting - NOT INSTALLED by default.
# Replace <repo-path> and <log-dir>, review, then enable on the Docker host
# with:  crontab -e  (paste the line below)
#
# Every 5 minutes: reconcile prior drafts, then draft replies for new mail.
# Safety: --max-drafts-per-run 3 baked into the bridge defaults; every run
# writes a summary row to the runs table and appends to the log below.
#
# */5 * * * * cd <repo-path>/nas && /usr/bin/docker compose run --rm bridge >> <log-dir>/draft-replies.log 2>&1

# systemd-timer alternative (equivalent; use EITHER this or cron, not both):
# templates in nas/systemd/ - instantiation one-liner in nas/README.md.
